Popular Nigerian female disc jockey, Olawunmi ‘DJ Lambo’ Okerayi alongside other women in the Nigerian music sector have been billed to speak at ‘Women in Live Music Business in Nigeria Workshop.’ The event, which is hosted by Kontentt Live Limited, is scheduled to hold on January 31, at the Radisson Hotels, Lagos. DJ Lambo, it was gathered, will speak on the topic ‘Performance and Music Business.’ Other speakers include Moyosore Shomade, who will talk on ‘Backstage Management and Tour Management’, Omolola Oyedele will address the issues on ‘Contract Negotiation’, while ‘Yemisi Falaye will give a lecture on ‘Artiste Management.’   Nigerian Idol 7: Winner to get N100m as Binance, Bigi join…     Jaruma remanded after Regina Daniel’s husband petition     I suck at showing interest in people – Ex-BBNaija’s…   According to the organisers, the workshop is intended for young women, between the ages of 18 and 35, with an interest in a career in music, as well as other adjacent fields to the music business. - Advertisement - Kontentt Live’s project manager, Opeyemi Balogun said the workshop is put together to encourage women in the creative sector. “We’re choosing to focus on Women in the Nigerian Music Business because we recognise that women ‘behind the scenes’ in the industry don’t get adequate recognition and because we believe in equality and the capability of women in whatever field they choose to build their paths. “The workshop is led by the Music in Africa Live project, in partnership with the Music in Africa Foundation (MIAF). So, the live-streamed programme will end with the issuance of certificates of participation.”